---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout title="Privacy Policy – Barbier Berlin" lang="en">
  <section class="pt-32 pb-16 bg-surface-950">
    <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
      <h1 class="text-4xl font-display font-bold text-white mb-8">Privacy Policy</h1>
      <div class="space-y-8 text-white/70 text-sm leading-relaxed">

        <div>
          <h2 class="text-white text-xl font-semibold mb-3">1. Controller</h2>
          <p>
            Barbier Berlin<br />
            Markgrafenstraße 88, 10969 Berlin<br />
            Email: info@barbier.berlin<br />
            Phone: 030 259 265 00
          </p>
        </div>

        <div>
          <h2 class="text-white text-xl font-semibold mb-3">2. Collection and Storage of Personal Data</h2>
          <p>
            When using our website and booking system, we collect the following data:
          </p>
          <ul class="list-disc list-inside mt-2 space-y-1">
            <li>Account data (name, email address, phone number) upon registration</li>
            <li>Booking data (selected service, date, time)</li>
            <li>Usage data (points balance, booking history)</li>
            <li>Technical data (IP address, browser type) via server logs</li>
          </ul>
        </div>

        <div>
          <h2 class="text-white text-xl font-semibold mb-3">3. Purpose of Data Processing</h2>
          <ul class="list-disc list-inside space-y-1">
            <li>Processing and managing appointment bookings</li>
            <li>Managing your customer account and loyalty program</li>
            <li>Appointment confirmations and reminders by email</li>
            <li>Improving our services</li>
          </ul>
        </div>

        <div>
          <h2 class="text-white text-xl font-semibold mb-3">4. Legal Basis</h2>
          <p>
            Your data is processed on the basis of Art. 6(1)(b) GDPR (performance of a contract)
            and Art. 6(1)(a) GDPR (consent).
          </p>
        </div>

        <div>
          <h2 class="text-white text-xl font-semibold mb-3">5. Data Storage and Deletion</h2>
          <p>
            Your data is stored on servers in the European Union (Cloudflare, EU data centres).
            Personal data is deleted once the purpose of storage no longer applies,
            provided no statutory retention obligations exist.
          </p>
          <p class="mt-2">
            Loyalty points expire after 6 months without an active booking.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div>
          <h2 class="text-white text-xl font-semibold mb-3">6. Your Rights</h2>
          <p>You have the following rights regarding your personal data:</p>
          <ul class="list-disc list-inside mt-2 space-y-1">
            <li>Right of access (Art. 15 GDPR)</li>
            <li>Right to rectification (Art. 16 GDPR)</li>
            <li>Right to erasure (Art. 17 GDPR)</li>
            <li>Right to restriction of processing (Art. 18 GDPR)</li>
            <li>Right to data portability (Art. 20 GDPR)</li>
            <li>Right to object (Art. 21 GDPR)</li>
          </ul>
          <p class="mt-2">
            To exercise your rights, please contact: info@barbier.berlin
          </p>
        </div>

        <div>
          <h2 class="text-white text-xl font-semibold mb-3">7. Cookies</h2>
          <p>
            We only use technically necessary cookies (session cookies for login).
            No tracking or marketing cookies are used.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div>
          <h2 class="text-white text-xl font-semibold mb-3">8. SSL Encryption</h2>
          <p>
            This website uses SSL encryption (HTTPS) for security reasons.
            An encrypted connection is indicated by the padlock symbol in the address bar.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div>
          <h2 class="text-white text-xl font-semibold mb-3">9. Hosting</h2>
          <p>
            Our website is hosted on Cloudflare Pages. Cloudflare operates data centres
            in the EU and processes data in accordance with GDPR.
          </p>
        </div>

        <p class="text-white/40 text-xs pt-4 border-t border-white/5">
          Last updated: April 2026
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</Layout>
